 {"id":"bd-13ws","title":"Harmonize API Response Envelope","description":"## Overview

Create a unified API response envelope used by both CLI and daemon for consistent agent parsing.

## Problem

Currently:
- CLI uses `JsonResponse<T>` with `{version, command, success, data, error}`
- Daemon returns raw types directly without envelope

Agents must handle two different response formats.

## Additional Scope (Merged from bd-23a1)

Resolve the **StatusResponse naming collision** across rch/rchd/rch-common:
- Ensure no two public types share the same `StatusResponse` name in different modules
- Prefer explicit names (e.g., `CliStatusResponse`, `DaemonStatusResponse`) or module-qualified exports
- Update serde tags and re-exports to avoid ambiguous type references in downstream crates
- Add unit tests to lock down the new names and serialization output

## Solution

1. Create `rch-common/src/api/response.rs` with shared `ApiResponse<T>` type
2. Define single envelope format for ALL responses
3. Update CLI to use `ApiResponse<T>` instead of `JsonResponse<T>`
4. Daemon already uses untagged enum pattern - keep it but use `ApiError` for errors

## ApiResponse Design

```rust
/// Unified API response envelope.
#[derive(Debug, Clone, Serialize, Deserialize)]
pub struct ApiResponse<T: Serialize> {
    /// API version for compatibility detection.
    pub api_version: &'static str,  // "1.0"

    /// Unix timestamp when response was generated.
    pub timestamp: u64,

    /// Optional request ID for correlation/tracing.
    #[serde(skip_serializing_if = "Option::is_none")]
    pub request_id: Option<String>,

    /// Command that produced this response.
    #[serde(skip_serializing_if = "Option::is_none")]
    pub command: Option<String>,

    /// Whether the operation succeeded.
    pub success: bool,

    /// Response data on success.
    #[serde(skip_serializing_if = "Option::is_none")]
    pub data: Option<T>,

    /// Error details on failure.
    #[serde(skip_serializing_if = "Option::is_none")]
    pub error: Option<ApiError>,
}
```

## Implementation Details

### Constructors

```rust
impl<T: Serialize> ApiResponse<T> {
    /// Create a successful response.
    pub fn ok(command: impl Into<String>, data: T) -> Self;

    /// Create a successful response without command name.
    pub fn ok_data(data: T) -> Self;

    /// Create an error response.
    pub fn err(command: impl Into<String>, error: ApiError) -> Self;

    /// Create an error response without command name.
    pub fn err_only(error: ApiError) -> Self;
}

impl ApiResponse<()> {
    /// Create a simple success response with no data.
    pub fn ok_empty(command: impl Into<String>) -> Self;
}
```

### Builder Pattern

```rust
pub struct ApiResponseBuilder<T: Serialize> {
    command: Option<String>,
    request_id: Option<String>,
    data: Option<T>,
    error: Option<ApiError>,
}
```

