 {"id":"bd-155i","title":"Idea: Worker capabilities report + mismatch warnings","description":"## Background
Workers may differ in runtimes (Rust/Bun/Node) and toolchain versions. Users need a clear report to understand compatibility and why selection might fail.

## Goals
- Add `rch workers capabilities` command to display runtime versions per worker.
- Highlight mismatches vs local toolchain and required runtime for a command.
- Provide JSON output for automation.

## Design / Approach
- Reuse existing worker `Capabilities` command from rch-wkr.
- Daemon caches capabilities; CLI queries daemon and formats report.
- Add warnings when required runtime missing or versions diverge significantly.

## Tasks / Subtasks
- Add CLI command and API call to fetch capabilities.
- Implement diff vs local toolchain (best-effort).
- Surface in `rch diagnose` output.

## Tests
- Unit: capabilities formatting and JSON output.
- Integration: mock worker returns capabilities and CLI renders warnings.
- E2E: capabilities command runs in mock mode.

## Acceptance Criteria
- Users can see worker runtime versions easily.
- Mismatch warnings are clear and actionable.

## Logging & E2E
- E2E script: scripts/e2e_bd-155i.sh (one script per bead unless intentionally combined).
- Logging format: JSONL via TestLogger (tests/true_e2e/logging.rs) or scripts/test_lib.sh log_json.
- Required fields: ts, test, phase, worker, command, bytes_transferred, duration_ms, result, error (if any).
- Phases to log (as applicable): classify, select, sync_up, exec, sync_down, cleanup, summary.
- Include a final summary block with pass/fail counts and total elapsed time.

## Edge Cases & UX
- Missing capability fields should display as "unknown" not error.
- Provide refresh flag to bypass stale cache.
- Mismatch warnings are informational, not fatal.

## E2E Outline
- Mock capabilities (rust/bun versions) -> report rendered correctly.
- Run `rch diagnose bun test` -> missing runtime warning.
- JSON output includes capability fields per worker.

## Unit Tests (Detailed)
- rch/src/commands.rs: capabilities formatting + JSON schema.
- rchd/src/telemetry.rs: capability cache refresh logic.

## E2E Script Notes
